as going to do. For one thing, she was going to spend a lot of time in here, just sitting thee enjoying herself.<br><br>She shivered, drawing her clozk about her tightly, really quite an elegant one, just like the rest of her style. It was midnight blue, and had pretty little roses swirling over it, intertwined together by vines. Her pants were velvet, but they were just plain black, and her shirt was just a pretty white little thing. To be honest, she looked more the part of an artist than of a lawyer, but a lawyer she was, and she was happy being such. Finishing her mocha, she walked out, just wandering about the street. <p><p align=center><font color="powderblue"><b>'The night is serene, sir, and so am I.'<br>~Jane, from <i>Jane Eyre</i></b></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCC0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/uwilhelmkruger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wilhelm Kruger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sharin's boyfriend<br>Such a sweetheart<br>She loves him SOOOO MUCH!!!</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#000000>(8/15/02 2:38:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fhoggiesreunionfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sipping Some Coffee</span><hr size=1> A figure had been watching her from the corner. Starlight blue eyes following the cup in her hands. The figure was covered in a dark grey uniform. A red eagle emblemed on the right shoulder. At his side lay a sheath with a silver saber. More for decoration then combat. Wilhelm took two steps toward her. Gliding as he did.  His sandy blond hair hung down over his eyes. He took a seat at the table next to her. It had been a while. Perhaps she had forgotten. Wilhelm had fought a war and lost. Worked to tear down a wall and failed. Wilhelm viewed his entire life as failure. Wilhelm looked at a bright blue right on his hand. It was a gift from berlin, a ring for valor on his field. Yet he sat alone. Those he had fought with had passed on. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFF0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/usharinmarr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sharin Marr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>All-Mighty Creator of the Board!<br>Bow Down to her<br>She loves Wilhelm!<br>Not-so-secretly HATES Dark CHocolate!<br>Thinks it looks like dog crap<br>GO WHITES!!!<br>Is a beautiful and wonderful administrator<br>Would never take away the admin powers of a certain chocolate leader<br>Is much to nice and wonderful to do that<br>Right???</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#000000>(8/15/02 2:56:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fhoggiesreunionfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.freeavatars.net/vpimages/brunettes/fhbl101.gif height=116 width=102></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sipping Some Coffee</span><hr size=1> Anna turned around, hearing a noice. She knew this café was barely populated, only by such bookworms as herself, so it was quite a surprise to hear someone else there. The face was familiar, yet utterly strange.<br><br>Sharin looked at the files she had with her in her briefcase, then at him, and then, a name popped into her head. &quot;Wilhelm Kruger,&quot; she whispered. Smiling, she went over to his booth and plopped into it, for no reason other than to talk. &quot;Wilhelm! Wonderful to see you again!&quot; she said, smiling.<br><br>The expression in her eyes changed from one of curiosity to one of happiness. &quot;It is marvellous to see you again. How have you been? Moreover, how are you?&quot; She smiled as she ordered another mocha to drink. How fond she was of those!<br><br>&quot;Want anything to eat? I can pay for it, I have the money. After all, with all those Death Eaters being captured, I really gain quite a lot.&quot;<br><br>She looked at his eyes, his almost haunted blue eyes. He had changed, had matured. &quot;Wilhelm, what's wrong?&quot; Anna asked, putting her warm hand on top of his. <p><p align=center><font color="powderblue"><b>'The night is serene, sir, and so am I.'<br>~Jane, from <i>Jane Eyre</i></b></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCC0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/uwilhelmkruger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wilhelm Kruger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sharin's boyfriend<br>Such a sweetheart<br>She loves him SOOOO MUCH!!!</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#000000>(8/15/02 3:03:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fhoggiesreunionfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sipping Some Coffee</span><hr size=1> Wilhelm pulled his hand away. Wilhelm looked up at her. Haunting eyes that seemed to not see her to see something else. He could see them still in his dreams. People dying in the streets. He could hear the echos at night of the people he could not reach the wall over with. Wilhlem lips barely moved, &quot;Times have changed . I have changed. I have lived my life and burried those I loved.  Betrayed those I befriended. Killed those I loved. I am nothing but a monster anymore. I cannot even feel the warmth of a fire&quot;. He sighed looking out at her breifcase. Wilhelm looked at his fist cold and torn. &quot;You fought the death eaters, I fought the world sharin&quot;. He turn not willing to look at her. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFF0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/usharinmarr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sharin Marr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>All-Mighty Creator of the Board!<br>Bow Down to her<br>She loves Wilhelm!